FOR the prevention of Clandeſtine and uncertaine Sales and Titles;
A. 52. P. 15.
 It is Ordered and Declared by this Court, That henceforth no Sale or Alienation of Houſes and Lands, within this Jurisdiction, ſhall be holden good in Law, except the ſame be done by Deed in writing, under hand and Seal,No ſale of Land vallid without Deed &cs and Delivered, and Poſſeſſion give upon part in the name of the whole, by the Seller or his Atturney, ſo Authorized under hand and Seal; unleſs the ſaid Deed be acknowledged and Recorded according to Law. [1652.]

